01:16:02,599 --> 01:16:04,476
- Ah, the one you were Ron.

1502
01:16:04,559 --> 01:16:06,478
Yeah, her husband
was just found dead.

1503
01:16:08,646 --> 01:16:11,149
- I'm sorry.
What happened? Where?

1504
01:16:11,232 --> 01:16:14,360
- The body was found in
Cabbage Alley off Chef Menteur.

1505
01:16:14,444 --> 01:16:15,820
- Possible drug deal gone bad.

1506
01:16:15,904 --> 01:16:18,823
Single bullet to the aorta.
A. 38.

1507
01:16:20,617 --> 01:16:22,077
- Phew!

1508
01:16:27,248 --> 01:16:28,458
- Gary?

1509
01:16:30,585 --> 01:16:32,545
- Yeah,
when I was researching her,

1510
01:16:32,629 --> 01:16:35,632
guy seemed like he had
a lot of drug problems.

1511
01:16:35,715 --> 01:16:36,758
So...

1512
01:16:38,635 --> 01:16:40,178
Any Suspects?

1513
01:16:40,261 --> 01:16:41,572
- Not really.
Sounds like she and the husband

1514
01:16:41,596 --> 01:16:43,515
got into it outside of
a bar called Virgo's,

1515
01:16:43,598 --> 01:16:46,184
and then the guy she was
with pulled a gun on him.

1516
01:16:48,144 --> 01:16:49,979
- Did we ID that guy?

1517
01:16:50,063 --> 01:16:51,272
- Not yet.

1518
01:16:54,109 --> 01:16:58,029
- Maybe it's a new,
uh, boyfriend or something?

1519
01:16:58,113 --> 01:17:01,699
Should we go try to
find this guy, talk to him?

1520
01:17:01,783 --> 01:17:03,451
- I'm liking that.

1521
01:17:03,535 --> 01:17:04,720
Let us know what you find out.

1522
01:17:04,744 --> 01:17:08,081
- I think Johnson
and I should tag-team this.

1523
01:17:08,164 --> 01:17:11,543
Is that all right
if I bring him?

1524
01:17:11,626 --> 01:17:12,752
- Sure.

1525
01:17:12,836 --> 01:17:14,337
- Are you cool with it, Gary?

1526
01:17:16,840 --> 01:17:18,341
- Yeah.

1527
01:17:46,828 --> 01:17:47,912
- What are you doing?

1528
01:17:47,996 --> 01:17:50,081
- Oh.
Looking for the boyfriend...

1529
01:17:56,004 --> 01:17:57,922
Oh Shit! I found him!

1530
01:17:58,006 --> 01:17:59,299
Fuck! I'm good.

1531
01:17:59,382 --> 01:18:01,718
- C'mon.
What... what are we doing here?

1532
01:18:01,801 --> 01:18:02,927
- (Hey, hey, hey. he)!-

1533
01:18:03,011 --> 01:18:04,846
Look, I'm... I'm not
going to tell anybody.

1534
01:18:04,929 --> 01:18:06,222
- Tell 'em what?

1535
01:18:06,306 --> 01:18:08,200
So, I ran into her again.
Doesn't mean I'm the boyfriend.

1536
01:18:08,224 --> 01:18:09,910
Doesn't mean I have
anything to do with anything.

1537
01:18:09,934 --> 01:18:11,686
- Whoa, whoa, whoa.

1538
01:18:11,769 --> 01:18:13,646
Whoa. So defensive.

1539
01:18:13,730 --> 01:18:16,441
Look, no... nobody's
accusing you of anything.

1540
01:18:16,524 --> 01:18:20,153
I was just... I was just
wondering if you, uh...

1541
01:18:20,236 --> 01:18:21,487
You knew this guy?

1542
01:18:21,571 --> 01:18:23,406
If he looked familiar?

1543
01:18:25,283 --> 01:18:28,786
- Yeah, that was the guy that
ran out of the restaurant...

1544
01:18:28,870 --> 01:18:31,080
What was his name? Mike?

1545
01:18:31,164 --> 01:18:34,209
- Ray...
He's Madison's husband.

1546
01:18:34,292 --> 01:18:35,543
Right?

1547
01:18:37,795 --> 01:18:40,173
- Right.

1548
01:18:40,256 --> 01:18:41,525
- You see, I went back
and listened

1549
01:18:41,549 --> 01:18:43,092
to that conversation
that you guys had,

1550
01:18:43,176 --> 01:18:46,596
and it just took on
a whole different

1551
01:18:46,679 --> 01:18:48,640
layer of meaning for me.

1552
01:18:48,723 --> 01:18:50,683
You really knew
what button to push

1553
01:18:50,767 --> 01:18:53,144
with that whole boyfriend
line, huh?

1554
01:18:53,228 --> 01:18:54,145
Huh?

1555
01:18:54,229 --> 01:18:55,730
- What are you getting at?

1556
01:18:58,316 --> 01:19:00,485
- Nothing. Nothing. It's just...

1557
01:19:00,568 --> 01:19:03,196
Hey, look, we're...
We're friends, right, Gary?

1558
01:19:03,279 --> 01:19:04,864
Let you in on something.

1559
01:19:04,948 --> 01:19:07,408
Over the years,
I've sort of learned to...

1560
01:19:07,492 --> 01:19:10,995
Follow my nose
on these hunches that I have,

1561
01:19:11,079 --> 01:19:14,207
and usually something
turns up pretty interesting...

1562
01:19:15,708 --> 01:19:16,876
valuable.

1563
01:19:17,752 --> 01:19:19,254
- Let me know what you find.

1564
01:19:21,589 --> 01:19:24,008
- Maybe.

1565
01:19:24,092 --> 01:19:27,053
All right.
Well, I don't know...

1566
01:19:27,136 --> 01:19:28,721
Nothing here.

1567
01:19:35,270 --> 01:19:36,479
You scared me.

1568
01:19:37,772 --> 01:19:38,898
- Hi.

1569
01:19:41,734 --> 01:19:44,821
- Why are you
looking at me like that?

1570
01:19:44,904 --> 01:19:46,364
- Like what?

1571
01:19:46,447 --> 01:19:48,992
- You're looking at me
like something's wrong.

1572
01:19:49,075 --> 01:19:50,785
- Is something wrong?

1573
01:19:52,954 --> 01:19:55,373
Anything out of the ordinary?

1574
01:19:55,456 --> 01:19:57,041
- Okay, what are...
What are you doing?

1575
01:19:57,125 --> 01:19:59,252
Look, Ron, it's too early
for this shit.

1576
01:19:59,335 --> 01:20:01,004
- Did you hear about Ray?

1577
01:20:03,464 --> 01:20:07,552
- That he's dead? Yeah.

1578
01:20:07,635 --> 01:20:09,345
How do you know about that?

1579
01:20:09,429 --> 01:20:11,222
- I just know.

1580
01:20:11,306 --> 01:20:12,449
Were you ever going to tell me?

1581
01:20:12,473 --> 01:20:16,394
You just didn't think
it would come up?

1582
01:20:16,477 --> 01:20:18,438
- Yeah, but who told you?

1583
01:20:19,814 --> 01:20:21,524
- This is sort of my area.

1584
01:20:21,607 --> 01:20:23,693
You know, I listen
to police scanners.

1585
01:20:23,776 --> 01:20:26,279
I tend to know who's being
killed in this town.

1586
01:20:27,989 --> 01:20:30,575
I'm wondering if you're okay
'cause you seem weirdly okay.

1587
01:20:30,658 --> 01:20:32,952
- I was obviously
going to tell you.

1588
01:20:35,288 --> 01:20:38,708
It's just that I'm still
just processing it all.

1589
01:20:40,877 --> 01:20:42,628
I don't really know
what to do with it.

1590
01:20:42,712 --> 01:20:46,257
You know, it's a weird position
to be in.

1591
01:20:46,341 --> 01:20:48,217
Am I supposed to be playing
the role of

1592
01:20:48,301 --> 01:20:49,301
a grieving widow?

1593
01:20:49,344 --> 01:20:52,472
Well, I don't know
how to pretend.

1594
01:20:53,556 --> 01:20:55,892
Was he a good guy? No.

1595
01:20:55,975 --> 01:21:00,772
Did I love him?
I mean, I loved him.

1596
01:21:00,855 --> 01:21:05,943
Just... people grieve
in different ways.

1597
01:21:06,027 --> 01:21:07,195
I just have to know.

1598
01:21:07,278 --> 01:21:09,822
Did you have anything
to do with this?

1599
01:21:09,906 --> 01:21:13,076
- Why the fuck would I have
anything to do with this?

1600
01:21:13,159 --> 01:21:14,869
What motive? You think...

1601
01:21:14,952 --> 01:21:16,287
I'm the one
who talked you out of

1602
01:21:16,371 --> 01:21:18,414
killing him
in the first place, remember?

1603
01:21:18,498 --> 01:21:20,218
What, you think
I'm just out there on my own

1604
01:21:20,291 --> 01:21:22,043
killing people for no money?

1605
01:21:22,126 --> 01:21:23,419
- Okay.

1606
01:21:24,962 --> 01:21:26,589
I just had to ask.

1607
01:21:30,676 --> 01:21:32,011
I'm sorry.

1608
01:21:35,598 --> 01:21:37,183
- It's okay. I'm...

1609
01:21:38,726 --> 01:21:40,269
I understand.

1610
01:21:46,901 --> 01:21:48,319
Come here.

1611
01:21:50,738 --> 01:21:53,574
- I'm really happy you're here.

1612
01:21:53,658 --> 01:21:54,742
- Me, too.

1613
01:21:57,203 --> 01:21:59,080
So, what happened?

1614
01:21:59,163 --> 01:22:00,998
Police call you to let you know?

1615
01:22:01,082 --> 01:22:02,834
- Yeah.

1616
01:22:02,917 --> 01:22:04,836
- And what are they saying?
Any suspects?

1617
01:22:04,919 --> 01:22:07,171
Arrests?

1618
01:22:07,255 --> 01:22:09,841
- They think there was
a drug deal going on.

1619
01:22:09,924 --> 01:22:11,342
They just found him shot.

1620
01:22:11,426 --> 01:22:12,510
- Hmm.

1621
01:22:15,096 --> 01:22:16,806
- I'm so scared.

1622
01:22:16,889 --> 01:22:18,558
- I know.

1623
01:22:18,641 --> 01:22:20,143
It's so weird,

1624
01:22:22,228 --> 01:22:23,771
so out of the blue.

1625
01:22:27,275 --> 01:22:29,610
But you don't have to be scared.
Why would you be scared?

1626
01:22:33,489 --> 01:22:35,032
- Because I killed him.

1627
01:22:41,747 --> 01:22:43,708
- You killed him?

1628
01:22:43,791 --> 01:22:44,959
- Yeah.

1629
01:22:47,128 --> 01:22:49,881
- Why would you do that?

1630
01:22:49,964 --> 01:22:53,634
- You told me yourself.
He was gonna come and kill me!

1631
01:22:53,718 --> 01:22:54,844
- So,

1632
01:22:54,927 --> 01:22:57,013
He was attacking you.
It was like self-defense.

1633
01:22:57,096 --> 01:22:58,556
- Technically...
- Technically, what?

1634
01:22:58,639 --> 01:23:00,224
What was he doing?

1635
01:23:00,308 --> 01:23:04,479
- He... he was either
passed out or asleep.

1636
01:23:04,562 --> 01:23:06,397
- And you killed him?

1637
01:23:06,481 --> 01:23:07,648
- Yeah.

1638
01:23:07,732 --> 01:23:10,067
I made a story,
and they're believing it.

1639
01:23:10,151 --> 01:23:12,195
- Oh my god...

1640
01:23:12,278 --> 01:23:15,781
Oh my god!

1641
01:23:16,491 --> 01:23:18,177
- Why are you getting
so worked up about this?

1642
01:23:18,201 --> 01:23:19,401
You do this shit all the time.

1643
01:23:19,452 --> 01:23:20,637
- I don't do this all the time.

1644
01:23:20,661 --> 01:23:23,539
I've never done this.
I've never killed anyone.

1645
01:23:23,623 --> 01:23:25,750
- What are you talking about?

1646
01:23:25,833 --> 01:23:27,335
- I'm a fake hitman.

1647
01:23:29,337 --> 01:23:32,548
That's why I didn't
put you away.

1648
01:23:32,632 --> 01:23:33,758
I didn't have you arrested.

1649
01:23:33,841 --> 01:23:37,553
Because I was working
undercover.

1650
01:23:37,637 --> 01:23:39,096
- You're a cop?

1651
01:23:39,180 --> 01:23:42,517
- No. I...

1652
01:23:43,684 --> 01:23:44,852
I teach at a college.

1653
01:23:44,936 --> 01:23:46,455
This hitman thing's
just like a part-time gig.

1654
01:23:46,479 --> 01:23:48,689
That's... gotten out of hand.

1655
01:23:48,773 --> 01:23:51,275
- So, you've been lying to me
this whole time?

1656
01:23:54,946 --> 01:23:56,447
I was stuck.

1657
01:23:57,949 --> 01:24:01,118
I didn't want to lose you,
and you met Ron first.

1658
01:24:01,202 --> 01:24:03,246
And-and... and you liked Ron...

1659
01:24:03,329 --> 01:24:07,083
I liked Ron. So, I didn't
want to show you Gary.

1660
01:24:07,166 --> 01:24:09,544
- Who the fuck is Gary?

1661
01:24:09,627 --> 01:24:11,212
- I'm Gary.

1662
01:24:11,295 --> 01:24:13,130
- I don't even know your name?

1663
01:24:13,214 --> 01:24:15,091
- My real name is Gary Johnson.

1664
01:24:16,551 --> 01:24:18,803
- Gary?
- I know!

1665
01:24:20,721 --> 01:24:21,973
- Oh.
- Sorry.

1666
01:24:22,056 --> 01:24:24,100
They've called three times.

1667
01:24:24,976 --> 01:24:25,994
- Something must be going on.

1668
01:24:26,018 --> 01:24:28,813
A... a situation probably...

1669
01:24:28,896 --> 01:24:30,356
Hey, how's it going, Claude?

1670
01:24:30,439 --> 01:24:31,607
Gary, where are you?

1671
01:24:31,691 --> 01:24:33,693
<i>We need you back
at the station now.</i>

1672
01:24:33,776 --> 01:24:35,194
- Now?
- Yes, now.

1673
01:24:35,278 --> 01:24:37,947
<i>We got a new development
on this Madison Masters.</i>

1674
01:24:40,866 --> 01:24:43,703
- Okay...
I'll be right there.

1675
01:24:43,786 --> 01:24:44,704
I'm sorry. Um...

1676
01:24:44,787 --> 01:24:45,830
I'm gonna...

1677
01:24:45,913 --> 01:24:47,498
I gotta handle something
really quickly,

1678
01:24:47,582 --> 01:24:49,041
and then I'm gonna be
right back...

1679
01:24:49,125 --> 01:24:50,293
- Don't.

1680
01:24:51,043 --> 01:24:54,714
Just leave,
whatever your name is.

1681
01:24:57,174 --> 01:24:59,010
<i>I might have walked in as Ron,</i>

1682
01:24:59,093 --> 01:25:01,053
<i>but I left as Gary.</i>

1683
01:25:05,808 --> 01:25:08,060
Johnson's here!
Phil, briefing room.

1684
01:25:10,896 --> 01:25:12,690
Wait 'til you hear this.

1685
01:25:12,773 --> 01:25:15,109
- Hey! Lookin' good, Gary.

1686
01:25:21,991 --> 01:25:23,576
- Glad you could make it.

1687
01:25:25,703 --> 01:25:28,748
- This is looking more and more
like we messed this up.

1688
01:25:28,831 --> 01:25:33,502
Madison Figueroa is now
the number one suspect.

1689
01:25:33,586 --> 01:25:35,379
- Really?
- , Really,

1690
01:25:35,463 --> 01:25:38,132
Have a seat.

1691
01:25:38,215 --> 01:25:40,217
Tell him what we just found out.

1692
01:25:40,301 --> 01:25:41,719
- About six months ago,

1693
01:25:41,802 --> 01:25:43,971
Ray Masters increased
his life insurance policy

1694
01:25:44,055 --> 01:25:46,557
by one million dollars.

1695
01:25:46,641 --> 01:25:48,559
A policy in which, of course,

1696
01:25:48,643 --> 01:25:51,395
the wife was named
the sole beneficiary.

1697
01:25:51,479 --> 01:25:52,271
- Hmm...

1698
01:25:52,355 --> 01:25:53,415
- Now, the policy pre-dates

1699
01:25:53,439 --> 01:25:54,899
the initial
solicitation attempt,

1700
01:25:54,982 --> 01:25:56,376
but Homicide now believes
there might be

1701
01:25:56,400 --> 01:25:58,069
some connective tissue here.

1702
01:25:58,152 --> 01:25:59,153
Maybe after your meeting,

1703
01:25:59,236 --> 01:26:00,696
she coerced someone else
to do it,

1704
01:26:00,780 --> 01:26:02,507
or she did it herself.
- Well, that's what happens

1705
01:26:02,531 --> 01:26:03,908
when you let someone
off the hook.

1706
01:26:03,991 --> 01:26:04,909
Not helpful.

1707
01:26:04,992 --> 01:26:06,619
- And that was a long time ago.

1708
01:26:08,746 --> 01:26:11,415
- Gary, did you ever
talk to her again

1709
01:26:11,499 --> 01:26:13,250
after that time at the Please U?

1710
01:26:13,334 --> 01:26:16,545
- Yeah. Actually, I did.

1711
01:26:16,629 --> 01:26:17,797
You did?

1712
01:26:17,880 --> 01:26:18,798
When?

1713
01:26:18,881 --> 01:26:20,841
- Yeah, I ran into her
at Ted's Frostop.

1714
01:26:20,925 --> 01:26:22,593
She just thanked me
for helping her out,

1715
01:26:22,677 --> 01:26:24,220
giving her good advice.

1716
01:26:25,179 --> 01:26:27,973
Actually, that was the
night I ran into you.

1717
01:26:28,057 --> 01:26:29,517
You talked to her.

1718
01:26:31,310 --> 01:26:32,853
- You talked to her, too?

1719
01:26:33,854 --> 01:26:37,775
- Oh...
I didn't realize that was her.

1720
01:26:37,858 --> 01:26:40,152
- Yeah, that was Madison.

1721
01:26:40,236 --> 01:26:42,321
- Huh“.

1722
01:26:42,405 --> 01:26:43,656
Huh.

1723
01:26:43,739 --> 01:26:47,118
So, do you think she could be
involved in his murder?

1724
01:26:48,369 --> 01:26:49,286
- I mean,
there's always a chance,

1725
01:26:49,370 --> 01:26:51,622
but I would be very surprised.

1726
01:26:51,706 --> 01:26:55,459
She just seemed so happy.
She left her husband.

1727
01:26:55,543 --> 01:26:57,128
She got her own place.

1728
01:26:58,629 --> 01:27:00,756
And just seemed like
she was doing really well.

1729
01:27:03,217 --> 01:27:05,177
- So, what are we doin'
next here, guys?

1730
01:27:06,220 --> 01:27:08,013
Well,

1731
01:27:08,097 --> 01:27:10,391
we could pull her in
for questioning at any time.

1732
01:27:10,474 --> 01:27:13,227
She'll probably
just get a lawyer, clam up...

1733
01:27:13,310 --> 01:27:14,645
and if she's really behind this,

1734
01:27:14,729 --> 01:27:17,398
she's probably got all her lies
and alibis in order. You know.

1735
01:27:17,481 --> 01:27:19,608
I'm thinking we got
a one-time opportunity

1736
01:27:19,692 --> 01:27:21,777
to get the unvarnished
story from her.

1737
01:27:24,029 --> 01:27:26,323
This guy.

1738
01:27:26,407 --> 01:27:27,992
- Me?
- Yeah.

1739
01:27:29,243 --> 01:27:33,956
Question: -When you...
Was it, ran into her,

1740
01:27:34,039 --> 01:27:36,500
were... were you Gary,
or were you the hitman?

1741
01:27:36,584 --> 01:27:39,170
Which one were you
going under on that one?

1742
01:27:39,253 --> 01:27:41,213
- Ron.

1743
01:27:41,297 --> 01:27:43,883
- Okay, so you're still
Ron, the hitman, to her?

1744
01:27:44,633 --> 01:27:46,260
- Who else would I be?

1745
01:27:48,554 --> 01:27:51,682
This is great. I mean, look,
she forever knows

1746
01:27:51,766 --> 01:27:55,060
that he knows
that she wanted to kill the guy,

1747
01:27:55,144 --> 01:27:58,522
and she must like him
or trust him enough

1748
01:27:58,606 --> 01:28:01,984
to be sharing a sundae
at Ted's Frostop.

1749
01:28:02,067 --> 01:28:03,194
I mean, let's face it, huh?

1750
01:28:03,277 --> 01:28:05,529
They... they got the goods
on each other.

1751
01:28:05,613 --> 01:28:08,491
I mean, she would never
in a million years suspect

1752
01:28:08,574 --> 01:28:09,843
he's recording
their conversation.

